    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Add a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until the oil is very hot</p><p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries, then pat the <strong>fries</strong> dry with<strong> kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Tip: This helps the fries get extra crispy!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>gravy base </strong>in 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>gravy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the oil is very hot, remove the tray from the oven and carefully add the <strong>fries</strong> to the hot oil</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a gentle mix up until the fries are coated in the oil</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 20-25 min or until the fries are golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat the<strong> sirloin steaks</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong>, drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>sirloin steak[s]</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Once the steaks are cooked, transfer to a plate to rest (save the pan!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the steak is cooking, add the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped mushrooms </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until golden</p><p>Once golden, add the <strong>gravy stock </strong>and <strong>clotted cream</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until thickened slightly</p><p>Once thickened add your <strong>truffle oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>truffled mushroom sauce</strong></p><p>Slice the rested steak finely on a clean board</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/21-day-aged-sirloin-steak-with-truffled-mushroom-sauce-with-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sirloin steak</strong> with the <strong>fries</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the side</p><p>Pour the <strong>truffled mushroom sauce</strong> over the steak</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
